<strong>WORKS CITED</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a &#8216;Works Cited&#8217; entry at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body 
of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Author&#8217;s Names. <em>Title of Book</em>. Place of Publication: Publisher, 
	year of publication. Medium of publication.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Author&#8217;s Names">Smith, Albaraa, Jack Spratt, and Johnny Horner</span>. 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Book">Who Stole the Pies?</span></em> 
	<span class="hover" title="Place of Publication">Sydney</span>: 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">New Media P</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="year of publication">2056</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Medium of publication">Print</span>.
</blockquote>
